# ===== REQUIRED: PostgreSQL database =====
# The server will NOT start without this. It's a full connection string to a
# Postgres database (hosted services like Neon/Render/Supabase work great and are
# free to start). SSL is used automatically when this is set.
#   Format: postgres://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DATABASE
# Example (Neon): postgres://user:pass@ep-xxxx.us-east-2.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL=

ADMIN_EMAIL=your_email@example.com
VITE_ADMIN_EMAIL=your_email@example.com
PORT=5006
APP_URL=http://localhost:5173

# Email Service Configuration (optional - uses Ethereal test service if not set)
# For production, set one of:
# - SENDGRID_API_KEY=your_sendgrid_api_key
# - GMAIL_EMAIL=your_email@gmail.com and GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=your_app_password
EMAIL_FROM=noreply@ageofshadows.game
